@DATABASE "pnmalias.guide"
@INDEX "ImageEditor.guide/INDEX"
@FONT helvetica.font 13
@SMARTWRAP

@NODE MAIN "ImageEditor - Operator: Antialias [pnmalias]"
@TOC "Operator.guide/MAIN"

@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}Antialias@{UB}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}Antialias a portable anymap.@{UB}@{LINE}
@{PAR}Reads a portable anymap as input, and applies anti-aliasing to background and foreground pixels.
If the input file is a portable bitmap, the output anti-aliased image is promoted to a graymap.@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}Background and Foreground Color.@{UB}@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
Pixels with these values will be anti-aliased. By default,
the background color is taken to be black, and foreground color is assumed to be white.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{B}Blureweight.@{UB}@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
The central weight for the aliasing filter. It must be in the range of 1 to 99%.
The lower the value is, the "blurrier" the output image is.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{B}Surrounding.@{UB}@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
Apply anti-aliasing to all pixels surrounding background, or foreground pixels.
By default, anti-aliasing takes place only among neighboring background and foreground pixels.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}See also @{" Convolve " LINK "pnmconvol.guide/MAIN"}.@{LINE}
